David Minns Cc Minns has joined ECT Legal as Senior Legal Counsel for the Enron Australia office in Sydney He previously was Senior Counsel with Woodside Petroleum Limited in Perth Western Australia where he primarily focused on transactions involving oil gas transactions and financial derivatives For Enron Australia he will be focusing on the legal aspects of the commodity trading and marketing transactions eg gas power coal and financial derivatives arising out of the Australia office He will be a member of the Emerging Markets Group reporting to Alan Aronowitz Davids phone number is and fax number is

YK Representations Warrantiesthat we are past the end of the year rollover a question has been raised concerning whether or not YK representations and warranties should be given or requested in connection with acquisitions and divestitures It is our recommendation that no special YK representations be given or requested Obviously there may be situations in which some form of general representation or warranty may be appropriate with respect to the condition of computer hardware software and related systems In such situations we suggest that representations and warranties that are customarily used for the purchase or sale of computer hardware software and related assets be utilized If you have any further questions on this matter please contact Alan Aronowitz or Michael Robison Alan and Mike
